In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs and Treasury Secretary Tim Geithner discussed financial reform and the progress being made towards passing a comprehensive bill. Geithner emphasized the need for sweeping reforms to prevent future financial crises and expressed confidence that a strong bill was close to being finalized. He also addressed concerns about the national debt and the effectiveness of the mortgage modification program. Gibbs addressed criticism from Republicans about the administration's approach to financial reform and reiterated the President's commitment to strong and effective legislation. The briefing also touched on other topics such as the Supreme Court nomination process and the NASA space program.